*ACTION FOR THE AWARENESS OF SEXUAL EXPLOITATION IN WOMENS KPOP*  Hey everyone, so as we all know, there are new people becoming Kpop fans every day which is great. However, this means there are lots of people who may not have the awareness of what goes on in the shadows of this industry. The truth is that trainees and Idols are often treated terribly by their companies through various means. This is seen both in boy and girl groups of course, but girls tend to take the brunt because of sexual harassment and exploitation from within the company and in the public eye.   FOR ANYONE NEW TO KPOP OR TO THIS INFORMATION:  I have compiled a list of videos lifting the voices of female Idol's and trainees who have felt the effects of this problem and felt compelled to speak about it. I encourage you to watch any or all of these videos and share this information in any way you feel safe in doing so. Please like this comment so others see it! We must come together on this issue and keep fighting for the humanity of women in Kpop. Please comment and discuss this too here. Post links to videos that contribute to the issue if you want!   ***SIGN THE PETITION BELOW AT THE VERY BOTTOM!!***   Thanks for your time, and I hope the future of Kpop is more humane for everyone. <3   WATCH ANY THESE PLEASE! >>>>>>>  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7nwoQEyihhw  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UoISkfDZKCU  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sj9ZAZwisz4  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KdOA5BCwBi0  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vBGcbap5Gr4  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SE9MsjQAZpA&t=801s  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=P2hG5sfe0mE&t=2s  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=K4htvWc2r1o  **** Petition: ****  https://www.change.org/p/change-the-way-kpop-idols-are-treated-by-their-agencies-give-human-rights-to-singers-who-bring-happiness-to-millions-of-people-all-over-the-world

Let's talk about oopsy and its history line, oopsy is inspired in the movie Ocean's 8 if you haven't watched ocean's 8, Debbie Ocean (the protagonist) is trying to commit the heist of the century at the Met Gala in New York: she wants to steal a necklace valued at more than 150 million dollars with her 7 member team, in oopsy Lucy is Debbie Ocean and the necklace is represented as the feather that you can see many times on the mv, all the oopsy stages and concept photos are inspired by this movie!! (Especially this one: https://youtu.be/u7jt13u1ROk)

The more I listen to this the more I find things to talk about.  -Can we please appreciate the aesthetics? The huge painting, the table scene, the mannequins, the lighting, the editing they all scream HARD WORK. All this team that worked for all the details, I see all of their hardship. -And the lyrics. Empowering, strong,feminine, fresh, so cool. - Their face beauty. Could they be described as korean beauty standards? no. I love that. We need this in 2021 kpop. -I love that their slim figures was NOT what make them look cool. Read that again and keep in mind that last decade's kpop feminine-cool-successful videos was about the appearance. I am so glad I didn;t saw that here.  -I Love that their outfits are cool and well matched. We see different styles individually  but also the stylist chose the group outfits to be black and white (basic colors) full body suits. As if they wanted to point out that they respect their own style and personality but they are also a group/ a whole. - I looove so much that the accessories are unusual, but some of them are not so distinctive. At the same time their hair colors are a mix of casual style but then there are some hair accessories/ colors not so usual. I MEAN ONCE AGAIN SEEMS LIKE THE MESSANGE IS THAT WE RESPECT EVERY OPINION/STYLE/PERSONALITY and I loved that. That is cool. Also their nails. I am so tired of too much nail art and I LOVED the fact that some girls had pure clean natural color nails.

Ki-lings, what's your favorite song from New Rules? Mine is sweet dreams :)
Weki Meki had an interview with a mexican magazine, since spanish is my first language, I traduced the interview to english so ki-lings around the world can understand it <3 Here is it: 2020 seems to be the busiest year for Weki Meki already with her third comeback, plus all of the songs they've shown are known to be very energetic. Was it difficult to work with songs full of energy?   YOOJUNG: It's difficult because it's a choreography full of energy, but I felt like I had to cheer up our Ki-Ling; thinking about that I tried even harder on stage. Yes, it is difficult, but I think I was grateful to everyone and for that I really enjoyed it.  RINA: We feel comfortable and we are very excited to get our energy out on stage.Â We also have fun with each other, I'm glad we are comfortable aroud each other and can focus on the stage. Every part is physically tired, but it was nice to enjoy it, as well as to make the introductions and expressions.   The new song "COOL" gives a different girl crush feeling than previously shown, gives an "expert" vibe in the industry. How did you feel about this new concept, was it cool?  SEI: When I first heard "COOL", it seemed like a very intense song and a bit darker than what we had been doing. It was a melody with a different concept that we had not tried, so I had many doubts, so I put a lot of effort so that it had our essence. I am so proud and happy that many fans accepted and liked it with the unique touch of Weki Meki. It was very cool!   After "The Paradise" from the HIDE and SEEK album, Suyeon has a new song of your own on this album.Â  What inspired or empowered you to compose "Just Us"? Did you have any difficulties?  SUYEON: Yes, on the last album "The Paradise" was a song that we wanted to compose with the sound of Weki Meki; this time we thought about writing a melody that we needed and that we wanted. So I wrote Just Us, thinking that it would be nice if we had a song that we could sing with our Ki-Ling at concerts later on.   So what was the song you most enjoyed recording? Tell us your funny anecdotes! (:   ELLY: "COOL". I remember when we recorded the English version of "FACTS (COOL Eng. Ver.)", I think it was the first time I recorded an English version, it was interesting and fun.   DOYEON:Â  Recording "100 FACTS" was the most fun, since I like English, recording a whole song in this language was a lot of fun for me.   'COOL' seems to have a strong meaning of Let's get out of the monotonous life in a cool way! Besides that, is there a message that Weki Meki wants to convey to her fans in other New Rules songs?Â    LUCY: Among the songs on the album is 100 FACTS, The English version of COOL. Originally, the demo version was in English, so it conveys the sentiments better, so I'd like to recommend it.   Is there a song that you would like your fans to hear from your new album? Why?Â    YOOJUNG: I would like to recommend Just Us. It contains memories of the time when we were trainees, as well as the love we have for each other; apart Suyeon composed it, and Rina, Lucy and me participated in the lyrics. So it is a very meaningful song.Â    LUA: I want you to listen to Just Us. The lyrics contain our memories from before we were Weki Meki to the present. I think if they listen to this song they will get closer to us.   Weki Meki has shown a variety of musicality.Â  Are there any other genres that you would like to try? How about Latin style music?   SUYEON: Since the eight members of Weki Meki have different personalities, we don't want to pigeonhole ourselves into one musical genre, we always want to show you new sides of our music.Â  Latin style music is really fascinating and charming; if we have the opportunity, we also want to sing in Latin style.   Any songs that you listen to frequently recently?Â  Of course, for K-Magazine it's "COOL" by Weki Meki. (:   ELLY: These days I listen to a lot of "Can't Sleep" by Jang Beom-June. I love the emotionality of this song, that's why I keep it on repeat all the time.   RINA: Lately I've been listening to "Without All the Traces of Time" by 015B.   If you could travel anywhere in the world right now, where would you like to go?Â    LUA: More than saying a country, I want to see and enjoy different cultures, that's why I want to travel the world! Instead of thinking first of 'I want to go' without knowing about the country, I prefer to go around the world, accumulate a lot of experience, and think 'I want to go again' to that part.   It may be a bit difficult given the current situation, but would you like to visit Mexico later? If so, what would you like to do the most?Â  Fans from Mexico and South America are always waiting for Weki Meki's visit!Â    SEI: I really want to go! I love Mexican food very much. I especially like quesadillas and guacamole, to the extent that I sometimes make guacamole to eat in the bedroom. If I have the opportunity, it is one of the countries that I want to visit, so yes or yes I want to meet the Ki-Ling of Mexico and create good memories.   What factor do you think makes Weki Meki look a little cooler than other groups?Â    LUCY: I think the element that makes Weki Meki cool is our presentation. As our coordination is good on stage, I feel like we can show them a perfect performance, I think we really do it perfect.   In "COOL", the next part is impressive: "We can change the rules, get rid of the boring ones". What are some boring rules for Weki Meki? What do you think this letter means to those who hear it little?  DOYEON: I think everyone has a convention that they want to break. For example, I like this style of clothing, but people's comments make me wonder if I really do, or I like a song, but they say "Do you listen to those kinds of songs?", And you feel that you cannot proudly say that you are. I hope that all of us who have had such an experience can escape the monotonous rules, and have the confidence to live our way.

Well, how do I say this, I always has this conception that all of the Produce 101 will have difficulties in promoting within a group and I'm half wrong, half right. (50/50)  But for this one. I need to applaud Fatingo for trying off something new. Weki Meki is getting better and better and with the Melbourne Bounce as the main selection for their title song is a daring move. For the music and compose element, this arrangement hit the spot IF the lyrics are in English. But yet Hangul (Korean) language killed off some of the vibe of this song as it didn't ride along with the beat and it's kinda off, especially during the hook part and the climax of this song.  But yet again, It's listenable as it has one of my favourite genre which is Bounce/Melbourne Bounce (don't refer it as ''sounds'')  7/10

Resep odading Bahan:   250 gr tepung terigu protein tinggi 1 butir telur 2 sdm gula pasir 2 sdm susu kental manis 2 sdm margarin 1 sdt ragi instan 70 ml air hangat Minyak goreng secukupnya  Cara membuat:   - Bahan biang: campur ragi instan dengan gula dan air hangat, aduk rata sampai gula dan ragi larut. Diamkan 10-15 menit sampai berbusa untuk menandakan ragi masih aktif. - Campurkan tepung terigu, telur, susu kental manis, margarin dan masukkan bahan biang sedikit demi sedikit, uleni sampai kalis dan tidak lengket ditangan. - Bentuk bulat dan diamkan selama 1 jam hingga mengembang. - Bentuk pipih memanjang dan diamkan lagi sekitar 15 menit dan potong kotak-kotak, oleskan permukaannya dengan air matang dan taburi gula. - Goreng odading sampai kecokelatan, angkat dan sajikan.

OK, yeah, Weki Meki is officially in my top 5 favorite groups, i was waiting for another comeback until i put them in the top 5, and this did it.   This is an AMAZING comeback.  Let's see...  First the video, well, they all look beautiful (a shame that Sei has just a little screen time), but they look amazing, this is one of those videos you cannot stop looking, you just cannot look away, is eye catching, very well made video, the colors, the lighting on point, i don't see a very hard camera work, but it works, i like the aspect ratio they used too.  Then, the song, just in the beggining you can hear that is gonna be good, those 4 first notes describe the song, strong kinda edm cool groovie song, the chorus is just as expected, PERFECT, the only part i don't quite like is that 1:11 part, those 2 lines are kinda like a Red Velvet song, it doesn't really fit in the song, but the rest is just great, the way that powerful chorus drops with that "COOL!" just after the build up is overwhelming, the bridge is also well made, the rap parts, the production behind this is very nice.  And finally, the choreo, i have to say im impressed that it looks like a boy group choreo, but hot, is agresive but sexy at the same time.   I think im gonna be "humming" this song for the next days, this is really catchy, WELL DONE Weki Meki and Fantagio!

QueensğŸ”¥ğŸ˜­ğŸ˜­
ğŸš¨ATTENTIONğŸš¨ Hello viewers!  I'm just here to inform everyone the following about how YouTube's view count system works. You may have heard rumors: - that using emojis freezes the view count - that youtube purposely freezes views on kpop M/Vs  These are both entirely *FALSE*! Emojis do *NOT* freeze anything on YouTube because they are in no way associated with the actual view count system that YouTube uses to tally their views! Comments have absolutely *NO* effect on view counts as well.  YouTube also does *NOT* purposely freeze views for kpop M/Vs. When a video gets a massive amount of views in a short time span, it causes the server to lag and the view count freezes until it can catch up and tally all of the views.   Also, for the first *24 HOURS* any video is uploaded to YouTube, a filter is in place to not count repeat views in a short time span. They consider this similar to botting, so precautions are put in place to only count organic views for the first *24 HOURS*.  There is an easy way around this if you would like to have multiple views counted. Just make sure to watch other videos in between before returning to this M/V. You could make a Weki Meki playlist for example and throw in a few different M/Vs along with this one and let it cycle through each video. Your views will be counted then!  Happy viewing and please keep yourselves informed with accurate information!
